		<rdfs:label>inoculum expansion in shake flasks recipe process operation</rdfs:label>
		<skos:definition>A process by which a seed cell culture (or cultivation of cells) is grown in a minimum volume and scaled up systematically under controlled conditions until specifications are reached (viable cell density and volume are sufficient) to inoculate to a larger scale.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Inoculum Expansion in Shake Flasks</CMCO:hasBlaName>
	</owl:Class>
	
