		<skos:altLabel>AEX load</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>The process fluid, at a specific pH and conductivity, that is introduced to an anion exchange column to facilitate the binding of the target molecule(s) to the positively charged functional groups of the chromatography resin.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>AEX Load</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Anion-Exchange Chromatography Load</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<AnnotationVocabulary:acronym>AEXL</AnnotationVocabulary:acronym>
	</owl:Class>
	
