		<rdfs:label>used in production of</rdfs:label>
		<rdfs:domain rdf:resource="&obo;BFO_0000040"/>
		<rdfs:range rdf:resource="&Core;MaterialProduct"/>
		<skos:definition>A relationship linking a material object to the product that is produced using it.</skos:definition>
	</owl:ObjectProperty>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0001087">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/CriticalQualityAttribute"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&qudt1;hasUnit"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&MDO;MDO_0008664"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>endotoxin level</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>An in-vitro assay used for the detection and quantitation of bacterial endotoxins in injectable products or implantable medical devices that will make direct or indirect contact with the bloodstream or spinal fluid.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Endotoxin</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Endotoxin (EU/mg)</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Endotoxin (EU/ml)</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Level of Endotoxin</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:altLabel>endotoxin measurement</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>Quantitative measure of bacterial endotoxins in parenteral products, typically assessed using the Limulus Amebocyte Lysate (LAL) test per USP, to ensure patient safety.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Endotoxin</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Endotoxin Measurement</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>Dotmatics</MDO:curation_source>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
		<MDO:curation_source>Sciligence</MDO:curation_source>
		<MDO:source_field_name>endotoxin</MDO:source_field_name>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0001354">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&Core;MaintainableMaterialItem"/>
		<rdfs:label>master cell bank</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>A collection of cells derived from a single cell clone, which are stored under defined conditions.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Master Bank</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:definition>A cryopreserved, well-characterized cell stock derived from a single clone, serving as the original source for all production batches to ensure genetic stability and reproducibility.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Master Cell Bank</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<MDO:curation_source>Sciligence</MDO:curation_source>
		<AnnotationVocabulary:acronym>MCB</AnnotationVocabulary:acronym>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0001355">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&Core;MaintainableMaterialItem"/>
		<rdfs:label>working cell bank</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>A cell bank that is derived from the Master Cell Bank (MCB) and is used in the actual production of biopharmaceutical products. It is prepared from aliquots of a homogeneous suspension of cells obtained from culturing cells from the MCB under defined culture conditions.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Working Bank</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:definition>A cell bank that is derived from the Master Cell Bank (MCB) and is used in the actual production of biopharmaceutical products. It is prepared from aliquots of a homogeneous suspension of cells obtained from culturing cells from the MCB under defined culture conditions.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Working Cell Bank</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<MDO:curation_source>Sciligence</MDO:curation_source>
		<AnnotationVocabulary:acronym>WCB</AnnotationVocabulary:acronym>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0001857">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;NCIT_C70815"/>
		<rdfs:label>formulation buffer</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>Buffers comprise an integral component of protein formulations. Not only do they function to regulate shifts in pH, they also can stabilize proteins by a variety of mechanisms. Addition of buffers can result in increased conformational stability of proteins, whether by ligand binding or by an excluded solute mechanism.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:definition>A buffer that maintains pH and stabilizes protein structure in drug formulations, often using histidine, phosphate, or citrate systems to prevent aggregation and degradation.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Formulation Buffer</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Formulation Buffer</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0002336">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;BFO_0000019"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&qudt1;hasUnit"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&obo;UO_0000187"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>viability at harvest</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>Cell counter result data that quantifies the viability of the cells analyzed at harvest.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Harvest Viability</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Harvest Viability(%)</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:definition>Percentage of live cells in culture at the time of harvest, typically measured by trypan blue exclusion or automated cell counters, indicating culture health and productivity.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Cell Viability Within 24 Hours of Harvest</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Viability at Harvest</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>Dotmatics</MDO:curation_source>
		<MDO:source_field_name>harvest_viability</MDO:source_field_name>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0002403">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/CriticalQualityAttribute"/>
		<rdfs:label>potency</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>An expression of the activity of a drug, in terms of the concentration or amount needed to produce a defined effect; an imprecise term that should always be further defined ( EC50, IC50, etc.).</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Potency (mg API/unit)</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:altLabel>biologic activity</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>An expression of the activity of a drug, in terms of the concentration or amount needed to produce a defined effect; an imprecise term that should always be further defined ( EC50, IC50, etc.).</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Biologic Activity (Potency)</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<MDO:curation_source>DLC</MDO:curation_source>
		<MDO:curation_source>Excel</MDO:curation_source>
		<MDO:curation_source>GeneTox</MDO:curation_source>
		<MDO:source_field_name>potency</MDO:source_field_name>
		<MDO:source_field_name>potency_as_is</MDO:source_field_name>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0003226">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/LiquidChromatographyProcess"/>
		<rdfs:label>column load process</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>A weight or source of pressure borne by someone or something.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:definition>The amount of material (e.g., sample, buffer, or drug substance) applied to a process, influencing process performance and product quality.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Load</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Column Loading</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0003332">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&Core;InformationContentEntity"/>
		<rdfs:label>target value</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The value for the target.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:definition>A predefined quantitative goal for a process or product attribute, used to guide manufacturing control and ensure alignment with product specifications and quality standards.</skos:definition>
		<MDO:curation_source>Dotmatics</MDO:curation_source>
		<MDO:curation_source>SAIS/Pristima</MDO:curation_source>
		<MDO:source_field_name>target_val</MDO:source_field_name>
		<MDO:source_field_name>target_value</MDO:source_field_name>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0003532">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;NCIT_C70815"/>
		<rdfs:label>wash buffer</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>A reagent intended to wash away certain components while retaining others while causing no interference to the experimental procedure. These buffers are widely used in many applications, including ELISA, Western blot, immunohistochemistry, and purification.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:definition>A buffer used to remove unbound or non-specifically bound substances from chromatography resins.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Wash Buffer</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0003536">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;NCIT_C70815"/>
		<rdfs:label>elution buffer</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>A major solvent in affinity chromatography that is used to wash away unbound proteins at first and at a greater concentration it releases the desired protein from the ligand.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:definition>A buffer used in affinity chromatography to disrupt ligand-target interactions, enabling the release of bound proteins; commonly involves pH shifts or ionic strength changes.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Elution Buffer</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0003635">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.allotrope.org/ontologies/material#AFM_0000012"/>
		<rdfs:label>stock solution</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>A solution that is to be diluted to some lower concentration for actual use.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:definition>A concentrated solution of a substance used as a standardized source for preparing diluted working solutions, ensuring consistency and accuracy in experimental procedures.</skos:definition>
		<MDO:curation_source>DLC</MDO:curation_source>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
		<MDO:source_field_name>stock_solution</MDO:source_field_name>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0004197">
		<rdf:type rdf:resource="&owl;Class"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/CaptureStep"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/ReversePhaseChromatographyProcess"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&obo;BFO_0000066"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&CMCO;CMCO_0000091"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>protein A chromatography</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>High-performance liquid chromatography using protein A as the immobilized ligand as the affinity resin.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>HPLC-ProA</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:altLabel>HPLC protein A affinity chromatography</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:altLabel>protein A affinity chromatography</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>An affinity chromatography technique using immobilized Protein A to selectively bind the Fc region of antibodies, enabling high-purity capture of monoclonal antibodies during downstream processing.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Protein A Chromatography</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Protein A Chromatography</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:NamedIndividual>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0004710">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&Core;InformationContentEntity"/>
		<rdfs:label>material metadata</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>Metadata associated with the material.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Material Info</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Material Information</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:definition>Structured data describing the attributes, origin, and lifecycle of a material, including timestamps, user IDs, and audit trails, essential for traceability and data integrity in pharmaceutical manufacturing.</skos:definition>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0004886">
		<rdf:type rdf:resource="&owl;Class"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&MDO;MDO_0004887"/>
		<rdfs:label>CD CHO AGT medium</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>A protein-free, chemically-defined medium optimized for the growth of Chinese hamster ovary (CHO) cells and expression of recombinant proteins in suspension culture.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:altLabel>CD CHO AGT™ medium</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>A chemically-defined, protein-free medium with Advanced Granulation Technology, optimized for CHO cell growth and recombinant protein expression in suspension culture.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>CD CHO AGT™</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:NamedIndividual>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0004887">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/CultureMedium"/>
		<rdfs:label>CD CHO medium</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>A protein-free, serum-free, chemically-defined medium optimized for the growth of Chinese hamster ovary (CHO) cells and expression of recombinant proteins in suspension culture.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:altLabel>CD CHO liquid medium</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>A chemically-defined, serum-free medium designed for CHO cell growth and recombinant protein production, free of animal-origin components and suitable for DHFR amplification systems.</skos:definition>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0004987">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&CMCO;CMCO_0000108"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&obo;BFO_0000166"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&CMCO;CMCO_0000102"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&Core;isInputOf"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&CMCO;CMCO_0000102"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>shaker flask</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>A flask that has a characteristic shape to allow a good shaking performance without spilling liquid.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Erlenmeyer Flask</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Erlenmeyer Shake Flask</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Erlenmeyer Shaker Flask</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Shake Flask</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Shaker</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:definition>A conical vessel used in bioprocessing to culture cells in suspension under orbital agitation, facilitating oxygen transfer and mixing in early-stage development and screening.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>shake flask</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0005297">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&Core;InformationContentEntity"/>
		<rdfs:label>acceptance criteria</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>Conditions that must be satisfied for the work to be accepted.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Accepted Critia</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Passing Criteria</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:definition>Predefined numerical limits or conditions that a product or process must meet to be considered compliant with quality standards and suitable for its intended use.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Acceptance Criterion</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0005367">
		<rdf:type rdf:resource="&owl;Class"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/CellCultureExpansionProcess"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&obo;BFO_0000066"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&CMCO;CMCO_0000092"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>seed expansion in a bioreactor</rdfs:label>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Bioreactor Seed Expansion</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Seed Bioreactor Cell Culture Expansion</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Seed Expansion Bioreactor</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:altLabel>seed bioreactor expansion</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>The process of scaling up cell cultures from small vessels to larger bioreactors to achieve sufficient viable cell density for production inoculation, ensuring consistency and viability.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Seed Bioreactor</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Seed Bioreactor Expansion</CMCO:hasPkmName>
	</owl:NamedIndividual>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0005370">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/CellCultureExpansionProcess"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&obo;BFO_0000066"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&CMCO;CMCO_0000092"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>Inoculum Expansion</rdfs:label>
		<rdfs:label>inoculum expansion</rdfs:label>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Expansion of Inoculum</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:definition>A series of cell culture steps starting from thawed cell bank vials to generate sufficient viable cells for bioreactor inoculation, often involving multiple passages.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Inoculum Expansion</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Inoculum Expansion</CMCO:hasPkmName>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0005390">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&Core;PlannedProcess"/>
		<rdfs:label>pH adjustment</rdfs:label>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>pH Adjustment</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>pH Adjustment</CMCO:hasPkmName>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0005391">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&Core;PlannedProcess"/>
		<rdfs:label>conductivity adjustment</rdfs:label>
		<skos:definition>The process of modifying ionic strength in a solution to optimize conditions for chromatography or formulation, often by adding salts or buffers.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Conductivity Adjustment</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Conductivity Adjustment</CMCO:hasPkmName>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0005482">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.allotrope.org/ontologies/result#AFR_0000951"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&qudt1;hasUnit"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&obo;UO_0000032"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>hold duration</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The amount of time for which a particular condition or set of conditions is maintained.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Hold Time (Hr)</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Hold Time (min)</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Hold Time (s)</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:altLabel>hold time</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:altLabel>in-process hold time</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>The validated time period during which materials or intermediates may be held under specified conditions without compromising quality, safety, or efficacy.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Hold Time</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Hold Duration</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0005521">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/KeyProcessParameter"/>
		<rdfs:label>cell seeding density</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The amount of cells that are initially introduced into the flask/unit area.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Seeding Density (vc/cm2)</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Target Cell Seeding Density</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<oboInOwl:shorthand>Seeding Density</oboInOwl:shorthand>
		<skos:altLabel>seeding density</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>The initial number of cells introduced per unit area or volume in a culture vessel, critical for ensuring optimal growth, viability, and reproducibility.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Seeding Density</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0005533">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&Core;ProcessCharacteristic"/>
		<rdfs:label>population doubling level</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The number of times a population of cells has doubled since their initial isolation. It is used to track the cellular age and proliferation history of a cell line during in vitro or ex vivo culture.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:definition>The cumulative number of times a cell population has doubled during in vitro culture, used to track cellular age and ensure consistency in manufacturing.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Population Doubling Level</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
		<AnnotationVocabulary:acronym>PDL</AnnotationVocabulary:acronym>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0005596">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&Core;PlannedProcess"/>
		<rdfs:label>filter flushing</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>A process used to clean filters by removing accumulated contaminants. This is typically done by reversing the flow of fluid through the filter or using an external cleaning agent.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Filter Flush</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:altLabel>filter flush process</skos:altLabel>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Filter Flush</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Flush Filter</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>BioNX</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0005620">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/KeyProcessParameter"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&qudt1;hasUnit"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&obo;UO_0010052"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>transmembrane pressure</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>A measure of the difference in pressure between two sides of a membrane</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:definition>The pressure differential across a membrane during filtration, driving fluid flow and influencing filtration rate, fouling, and membrane performance.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Transmembrane Pressure</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Transmembrane Pressure</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>BioNX</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0005881">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;NCIT_C70815"/>
		<rdfs:label>histidine buffer</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>A buffer solution containing histidine.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0005984">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;UO_0000196"/>
		<rdfs:label>target pH</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The pH reading that is targeted for a process.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>pH Target</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:definition>The predefined pH value maintained during a bioprocess operation to optimize cell growth, protein stability, or reaction conditions, typically controlled via buffer systems.</skos:definition>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0006575">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;BFO_0000040"/>
		<rdfs:label>cell culture media component</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The component of the (growth/cell culture) media.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:altLabel>cell culture medium component</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:altLabel>media component</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:altLabel>medium component</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>Any ingredient in cell culture media, including salts, amino acids, vitamins, glucose, and growth factors, that supports cell survival, growth, and productivity.</skos:definition>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0006622">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&CMCO;CMCO_0000108"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&Core;isInputOf"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://ontology.merck.com/ontology/MMFGO/MMFGO_0000062"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>bulk drug substance container</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>A container that stores a bulk drug substance.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:altLabel>DS container</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:altLabel>bulk DS container</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:altLabel>drug substance container</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>A container used to store bulk drug substances (active pharmaceutical ingredients) prior to formulation or packaging, typically constructed from stainless steel, plastic, or glass-lined materials.</skos:definition>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0006627">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/KeyProcessParameter"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&qudt1;hasUnit"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&obo;UO_0000015"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>column diameter</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The diameter of the column.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:definition>The internal diameter of a chromatography column, which affects flow rate, resolution, and sample capacity; narrower columns offer higher sensitivity, while wider columns support larger sample volumes.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Column Diameter</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Column Diameter</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0006645">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.allotrope.org/ontologies/result#AFR_0001584"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&qudt1;hasUnit"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&obo;UO_0000027"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>hold temperature</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The temperature of the hold.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:definition>The specific temperature maintained during a hold period to preserve the quality and stability of intermediates or bulk products before further processing.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Hold Temperature</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Hold Temperature</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0006655">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/CriticalProcessParameter"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&qudt1;hasUnit"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&obo;NCIT_C25472"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>number of sanitization cycles</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The number of sanitization cycles.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:definition>The count of validated cleaning and disinfection procedures applied to equipment or systems to ensure microbial control and compliance with GMP standards.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Number of Sanitization Cycles</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Number of Sanitization Cycles</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0006669">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.allotrope.org/ontologies/result#AFR_0002036"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/CriticalQualityAttribute"/>
		<rdfs:label>product concentration</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The concentration of obtained product.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Product Concentration (mg/mL)</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:altLabel>final product concentration</skos:altLabel>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Product Concentration</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0006680">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&Core;PlannedProcess"/>
		<rdfs:label>sanitization process</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The process of cleaning and disinfection of an area or an item. Sanitizing involves the use of heat or chemicals to reduce the number of microorganisms to safe levels.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:definition>The process of cleaning and disinfection of an area or an item. Sanitizing involves the use of heat or chemicals to reduce the number of microorganisms to safe levels.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Sanitization</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Sanitization</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0006694">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/ThawingProcess"/>
		<rdfs:label>vial thaw process</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The process of allowing a vial to thaw to ambient conditions.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:altLabel>vial thaw into a shake flask</skos:altLabel>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Vial Thaw into a Shake Flask</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Vial Thaw</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0006696">
		<rdf:type rdf:resource="&owl;Class"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;CHEBI_23367"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&Core;hasRole"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&CMCO;CMCO_0000266"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>water for injection</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>Water of extra high quality without significant contamination.  It is used for the most critical pharmaceutical products and applications including mandatory use for injectable drugs, hemofiltration, irrigation, in the production of some active pharmaceutical ingredients, implantable medical devices and other varied applications.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:altLabel>ambient water for injection</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>Highly purified water produced by distillation or reverse osmosis, meeting USP and Ph. Eur. standards for endotoxin and microbial limits; used in parenteral drug manufacturing and cleaning.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>water for injection</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Water for Injection</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
		<AnnotationVocabulary:acronym>WFI</AnnotationVocabulary:acronym>
	</owl:NamedIndividual>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0006720">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/ProcessIntermediateMaterial"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&CMCO;hasInProcessControl"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.allotrope.org/ontologies/quality#AFQ_0000227"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&CMCO;hasInProcessControl"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&MDO;MDO_0001087"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&CMCO;hasInProcessControl"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&MDO;MDO_0009969"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&Core;isInputOf"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/ViralInactivation"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&Core;isOutputOf"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&MDO;MDO_0004197"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>protein A product</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The product resulting from protein A affinity chromatography.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:definition>A monoclonal antibody or Fc-fusion protein purified using Protein A affinity chromatography, which selectively binds the Fc region of IgG molecules.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Protein A Product</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Protein A Product</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
		<AnnotationVocabulary:acronym>PAP</AnnotationVocabulary:acronym>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0006722">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/LiquidChromatographyProcess"/>
		<rdfs:label>strip process</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The process of removing or &quot;stripping&quot; unwanted entities from a sample or specimen.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:definition>In chromatography, the process of removing bound impurities or residuals from a resin or membrane using a high-salt or low-pH buffer, often following elution.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Strip</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Strip</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0006748">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&CMCO;CMCO_0000108"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&obo;BFO_0000166"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&CMCO;CMCO_0000103"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&Core;isInputOf"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&CMCO;CMCO_0000103"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>rocker bag</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>A bag used for mixing or agitating liquids, solutions, cell cultures, etc. The bag typically has a flat rectangular shape and is placed on a rocker platform, which provides gentle agitation by rocking the bag back and forth.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Rocking Bioreactor Bag</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:definition>A single-use, flexible bioreactor bag placed on a rocking platform to culture suspension cells, providing gentle mixing and gas exchange for cell growth.</skos:definition>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0006878">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&Core;PieceOfEquipment"/>
		<rdfs:label>single use mixer</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>A mixer designed for single use, which helps to reduce the risk of contamination, decrease cleaning and validation costs, and eliminate equipment sterilization steps.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Single Use Stirrer</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:definition>A disposable mixing system used in biopharmaceutical manufacturing to prepare buffers, media, or intermediate products, minimizing contamination risk and eliminating cleaning validation.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Single Use Mixer</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
		<AnnotationVocabulary:acronym>SUM</AnnotationVocabulary:acronym>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0007042">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.allotrope.org/ontologies/result#AFR_0000951"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&qudt1;hasUnit"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&obo;UO_0000031"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>allowable pause duration</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The maximum duration that a process, system, or operation can be halted or paused without negatively affecting its overall functionality, performance, or outcomes.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Maximum Pause Duration</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Maximum Pause Time</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:altLabel>allowable pause time</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>The maximum validated time a process step may be paused without compromising product quality, safety, or efficacy, typically defined during process validation.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Total Pause Time</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Allowable Pause Time</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0007048">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;BFO_0000019"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&qudt1;hasUnit"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&MDO;MDO_0007608"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>transfer viable cell density</rdfs:label>
		<skos:altLabel>transfer cell density</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>The concentration of viable cells transferred from one vessel to another during scale-up or inoculation, typically measured in cells/mL and used to ensure consistent growth kinetics.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Viable Cell Density at Transfer</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Viable Cell Density at Transfer</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0007070">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;NCIT_C70815"/>
		<rdfs:label>equilibration buffer</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The buffer used for the equilibration process.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:definition>A buffer used to condition chromatography media to a defined pH and ionic strength before sample application, ensuring optimal binding conditions.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Equilibration Buffer</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0007078">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&Core;PlannedProcess"/>
		<rdfs:label>pre-equilibration process</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>Any step, event, or process occurring before the equilibration process.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:altLabel>pre-equilibration</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>A preparatory step before column equilibration, often involving buffer conditioning or resin stabilization to ensure consistent performance during chromatography.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Pre-Equilibration</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Pre-Equilibration</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0007082">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/ProcessIntermediateMaterial"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&Core;isInputOf"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&MDO;MDO_0004197"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&Core;isOutputOf"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/HarvestingProcess"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>harvest cell culture fluid</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The liquid medium that is obtained from a bioreactor or fermenter after the cell culture process. This fluid contains cells, cell debris, and the product of interest, such as proteins, antibodies, or other biologically active compounds that have been secreted or released by the cells.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>HCCF</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:altLabel>harvested cell culture fluid</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>The clarified liquid collected from a bioreactor post-culture, containing the product of interest, cells, and debris, typically processed by centrifugation and filtration.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Harvested Cell Culture Fluid</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
		<AnnotationVocabulary:acronym>HCCF</AnnotationVocabulary:acronym>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0007084">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/KeyProcessParameter"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&qudt1;hasUnit"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&obo;UO_0000015"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>column bed height</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The height of the packed bed of resin or other material within a chromatography column or filtration system.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:altLabel>bed height</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>The height of the packed bed of resin or other material within a chromatography column or filtration system.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Bed Hight</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Bed Height</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0007528">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/FiltrationProcess"/>
		<rdfs:label>ultrafiltration and diafiltration</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>A bioprocessing step for the purification, concentration, buffer exchange, and desalting of biomolecules such as proteins, antibodies, and nucleic acids. The techniques can be used separately or in combination to get the target molecule ready for the next processing step.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:altLabel>ultrafiltration/diafiltration</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>Membrane-based processes used in downstream purification to concentrate biomolecules and exchange buffers, typically using tangential flow filtration systems.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Ultrafiltration/Diafiltration</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Ultrafiltration and Diafiltration</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
		<AnnotationVocabulary:acronym>UF/DF</AnnotationVocabulary:acronym>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0007601">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;NCIT_C25709"/>
		<rdfs:label>pounds per square inch at the gauge</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The measured pressure relative to the current ambient pressure of the atmosphere.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Gauge Pounds per Square Inch</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Pound per Square Inch Gauge</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Pounds per Square Inch Gauge</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:altLabel>psig</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>A unit of pressure measurement relative to atmospheric pressure, commonly used in pharmaceutical equipment monitoring and validation.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>psig</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Pound per Square Inch Gauge</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0007604">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;NCIT_C25709"/>
		<rdfs:label>centimeter per hour</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>Centimeter per hour.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:altLabel>cm/h</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>A unit of linear flow rate used in chromatography to describe the velocity of mobile phase through a column, calculated from volumetric flow and column dimensions.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>cm/h</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Centimetre Per Hour</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0007608">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;NCIT_C25709"/>
		<rdfs:label>10^6 viable cells per milliliter</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The number of viable cells per milliliter of liquid.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:altLabel>10^6 vc/mL</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>A standard unit of cell concentration in culture, indicating one million viable cells per mL, typically determined using hemocytometer or automated counters.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>10^6 vc/mL</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>10^6 Viable Cells per Milliliter</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0007618">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;NCIT_C70815"/>
		<rdfs:label>dilution buffer</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The buffer used to dilute a sample or reagent to achieve a desired concentration without significantly altering the chemical environment of the sample.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:definition>A buffer that is used to reduce the concentration of a sample or reagent while maintaining its chemical environment, typically preserving pH and ionic strength.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Dilution Buffer</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Dilution Buffer</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0007652">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/CultureMedium"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&Core;isInputOf"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&CMCO;CMCO_0000102"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&Core;isInputOf"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&CMCO;CMCO_0000103"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&Core;isInputOf"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&CMCO;CMCO_0000104"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>medium for inoculum expansion</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The growth medium of the inoculum culture.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:altLabel>inoculum culture growth medium</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>A nutrient-rich solution optimized for cell growth and viability, used to expand the inoculum prior to bioreactor inoculation, often chemically defined and serum-free.</skos:definition>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0007848">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;BFO_0000029"/>
		<rdfs:label>manufacturing site</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>A pharmacutical manufacturing site.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Manufacturing Location</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:definition>A facility where pharmaceutical products are produced under GMP conditions, including equipment, personnel, and systems necessary for consistent quality and regulatory compliance.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Site Name</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0008096">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;NCIT_C70815"/>
		<rdfs:label>diafiltration buffer</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The buffer used for the diafiltration step or process.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:definition>A solution used during diafiltration to exchange the buffer environment of a retained biomolecule, typically matched in pH and ionic strength to the target formulation.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Diafiltration Buffer</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0008127">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/CultureMedium"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&Core;isInputOf"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/ProductionCultureProcess"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>production bioreactor growth medium</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The growth media used for the production bioreactor.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Production Bioreactor Growth Media</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:altLabel>production media</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>The growth medium used for the production bioreactor.</skos:definition>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0008357">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/ProcessIntermediateMaterial"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&CMCO;hasInProcessControl"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://purl.allotrope.org/ontologies/quality#AFQ_0000227"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&CMCO;hasInProcessControl"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&MDO;MDO_0001087"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&CMCO;hasInProcessControl"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&MDO;MDO_0009969"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&Core;isInputOf"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/ViralFiltration"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&Core;isOutputOf"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&obo;CHMO_0001209"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>anion exchange chromatography product</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>A product of an Anion-Exchange Chromatography process.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:altLabel>AEX product</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>A purified biomolecule obtained from anion exchange chromatography, where negatively charged species bind to positively charged resin and are eluted under controlled conditions.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>AEX Product</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
		<AnnotationVocabulary:acronym>AEXP</AnnotationVocabulary:acronym>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0008464">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/KeyProcessParameter"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&qudt1;hasUnit"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&MDO;MDO_0007601"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>differential pressure</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The difference in pressure that exists between two portions of fluid.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Difference in Pressure</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Pressure Difference</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Pressure Differential</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:definition>The pressure difference between two areas, used to control airflow and prevent contamination in cleanrooms and pharmaceutical environments.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Differential Pressure</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Differential Pressure</CMCO:hasPkmName>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0008590">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;UO_0000210"/>
		<rdfs:label>colony forming units per 10 milliliters</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>A unit of measure in Colony Forming Unit Per 10 Milliliter</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:shorthand>CFU/10mL</oboInOwl:shorthand>
		<skos:altLabel>cfu/10mL</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>A microbiological measure indicating the number of viable microorganisms capable of forming colonies in a 10 mL sample, used to assess contamination levels.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>cfu/10mL</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Colony Forming Unit Per 10 Milliliter</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0008626">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&Core;PlannedProcess"/>
		<rdfs:label>post-use integrity testing</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>A procedure used to verify the integrity of equipment after it has been used. For example, such test for a sterilizing filter ensures that the filter has not been compromised during use, which could allow contaminants to pass through.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:altLabel>post-use filter integrity test</skos:altLabel>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Post-Use Filter Integrity Test</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Post-Use Integrity Testing</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0008630">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&Core;PlannedProcess"/>
		<rdfs:label>controlled rate freezing</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>A method used to gradually freeze biological samples, such as cells or tissues, at a controlled, slow rate to preserve their viability and integrity. This technique is crucial in cryopreservation to minimize the formation of ice crystals, which can damage cell structures.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Controlled Rate Freeze</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:altLabel>controlled freezing</skos:altLabel>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Controlled Freezing</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Controlled Rate Freezing</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0008664">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&CMCO;CMCO_0000180"/>
		<rdfs:label>endotoxin units per milliliter</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>Endotoxin Units Per Milliliter</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:altLabel>EU/mL</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>A unit of measurement for bacterial endotoxin activity in a solution, determined by the LAL assay; 1 EU/mL = 0.1–0.2 ng/mL of endotoxin.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>EU/mL</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Endotoxin Units Per Milliliter</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0009123">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;BFO_0000040"/>
		<rdfs:label>cell culture media supplement</rdfs:label>
		<skos:altLabel>cell culture medium supplement</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:altLabel>media supplement</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:altLabel>medium supplement</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>An additive such as growth factor, amino acid, vitamin, or hydrolysate used to enhance cell growth, productivity, or stability in culture media.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Supplement</CMCO:hasPkmName>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0009127">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&CMCO;CMCO_0000109"/>
		<rdfs:label>proven acceptable range minimum</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>Minimum value of the Proven Acceptable Range.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:altLabel>PAR min</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:altLabel>PAR minimum</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>The lowest value of a process parameter is within a Proven Acceptable Range (PAR), where operation still ensures product quality and compliance.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>PAR Minimum</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0009128">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&CMCO;CMCO_0000109"/>
		<rdfs:label>proven acceptable range maximum</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>Maximum value of the Proven Acceptable Range.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:altLabel>PAR max</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:altLabel>PAR maximum</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>The highest value of a process parameter within a Proven Acceptable Range (PAR), ensuring consistent product quality when other parameters are held constant.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>PAR Maximum</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0009129">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&CMCO;CMCO_0000110"/>
		<rdfs:label>normal operating range maximum</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>Maximum value of the Normal Operating Range.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:altLabel>NOR max</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:altLabel>NOR maximum</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>The upper boundary of typical process variability that does not affect product quality, used to describe routine manufacturing conditions.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>NOR Maximum</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0009130">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&CMCO;CMCO_0000110"/>
		<rdfs:label>normal operating range minimum</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>Minimum value of the Normal Operating Range.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:altLabel>NOR min</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:altLabel>NOR minimum</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>The lower boundary of typical process variability that does not affect product quality, used to describe routine manufacturing conditions.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>NOR Minimum</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0009277">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;NCIT_C134263"/>
		<rdfs:label>target conductivity</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The target or desired conductivity value.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:definition>The desired conductivity value in a process solution, used to control ionic strength during chromatography, buffer preparation, or fermentation.</skos:definition>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0009665">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.allotrope.org/ontologies/material#AFM_0000012"/>
		<rdfs:label>sanitization solution</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>A solution or a liquid formulation used to clean and sanitize surfaces, equipment, or systems to reduce or eliminate microorganisms, such as bacteria, viruses, fungi, or other contaminants.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:definition>A validated chemical formulation used to reduce microbial contamination on surfaces or equipment in pharmaceutical environments, typically including alcohols, QACs, or oxidizing agents.</skos:definition>
		<MDO:curation_source>ELN</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0009964">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;BFO_0000019"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&qudt1;hasUnit"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&obo;UO_0000187"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>transfer viability</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>Cell counter result data that quantifies the viability of the cells analyzed at transfer.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Viability at Transfer</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:altLabel>transfer cell viability</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>The cell counter result data that quantifies the viability of the cells analyzed at transfer.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Viability at Transfer</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Transfer Viability</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0009965">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;BFO_0000019"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&qudt1;hasUnit"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&obo;UO_0000187"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>thaw viability</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>Cell counter result data that quantifies the viability of the cells analyzed at thaw.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>Viability at Thaw</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:definition>The percentage of viable cells immediately after thawing from cryopreservation, critical for determining the quality of the inoculum.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Viability After Thaw</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Thaw Viability</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0009969">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;BFO_0000019"/>
		<rdfs:subClassOf>
			<owl:Restriction>
				<owl:onProperty rdf:resource="&qudt1;hasUnit"/>
				<owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="&MDO;MDO_0008590"/>
			</owl:Restriction>
		</rdfs:subClassOf>
		<rdfs:label>bioburden</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>The number of viable microorganisms present in a product or on a surface that has not been sterilized.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:definition>The number of viable microorganisms present in a product or on a surface prior to sterilization; monitored to ensure microbial control in both sterile and non-sterile manufacturing.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Bioburden</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Bioburden</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0009970">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/CriticalQualityAttribute"/>
		<rdfs:label>filter integrity</rdfs:label>
		<obo:IAO_0000115>Quality and readiness of a filter. It is tested to confirm that filters retain their retentive properties and have not been damaged during handling, installation, or processing.</obo:IAO_0000115>
		<skos:definition>The ability of a filter to retain its specified performance characteristics, confirmed by tests such as bubble point, pressure hold, or diffusive flow before and after use.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>Post-Use Filter Integrity</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Filter Integrity</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
	<owl:Class rdf:about="&MDO;MDO_0010254">
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="&obo;NCIT_C25709"/>
		<rdfs:label>gram per liter resin</rdfs:label>
		<oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>g/L resin</oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym>
		<skos:altLabel>g product/L packed resin</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:altLabel>g/Lresin</skos:altLabel>
		<skos:definition>A unit expressing the dynamic binding capacity of chromatography resin, indicating how many grams of target molecule can be bound per liter of resin under defined conditions.</skos:definition>
		<CMCO:hasBlaName>g/Lresin</CMCO:hasBlaName>
		<CMCO:hasPkmName>Gram Per Liter Resin</CMCO:hasPkmName>
		<MDO:curation_source>PKM</MDO:curation_source>
	</owl:Class>
	
